<Link id="l00714" /><CodeLine lineNumber="714"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00715" /><CodeLine lineNumber="715"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Interface functions of this class map VOPD component operand indices</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00716" /><CodeLine lineNumber="716"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to indices of operands in MachineInstr/MCInst or parsed operands array.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00717" /><CodeLine lineNumber="717"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00718" /><CodeLine lineNumber="718"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Note that this class operates with 3 kinds of indices:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00719" /><CodeLine lineNumber="719"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - VOPD component operand indices (Component::DST, Component::SRC0, etc.);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00720" /><CodeLine lineNumber="720"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - MC operand indices (they refer operands in a MachineInstr/MCInst);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00721" /><CodeLine lineNumber="721"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - parsed operand indices (they refer operands in parsed operands array).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00722" /><CodeLine lineNumber="722"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00723" /><CodeLine lineNumber="723"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For SINGLE components mapping between these indices is trivial.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00724" /><CodeLine lineNumber="724"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// But things get more complicated for COMPONENT&#95;X and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00725" /><CodeLine lineNumber="725"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// COMPONENT&#95;Y because these components share the same</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00726" /><CodeLine lineNumber="726"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// MachineInstr/MCInst and the same parsed operands array.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00727" /><CodeLine lineNumber="727"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Below is an example of component operand to parsed operand</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00728" /><CodeLine lineNumber="728"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// mapping for the following instruction:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00729" /><CodeLine lineNumber="729"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00730" /><CodeLine lineNumber="730"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   v&#95;dual&#95;add&#95;f32 v255, v4, v5 :: v&#95;dual&#95;mov&#95;b32 v6, v1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00731" /><CodeLine lineNumber="731"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00732" /><CodeLine lineNumber="732"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                          PARSED        COMPONENT         PARSED</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00733" /><CodeLine lineNumber="733"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// COMPONENT               OPERANDS     OPERAND INDEX    OPERAND INDEX</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00734" /><CodeLine lineNumber="734"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// -------------------------------------------------------------------</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00735" /><CodeLine lineNumber="735"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                     &quot;v&#95;dual&#95;add&#95;f32&quot;                        0</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00736" /><CodeLine lineNumber="736"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// v&#95;dual&#95;add&#95;f32            v255          0 (DST)    --&gt;      1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00737" /><CodeLine lineNumber="737"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                           v4            1 (SRC0)   --&gt;      2</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00738" /><CodeLine lineNumber="738"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                           v5            2 (SRC1)   --&gt;      3</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00739" /><CodeLine lineNumber="739"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                          &quot;::&quot;                               4</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00740" /><CodeLine lineNumber="740"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                     &quot;v&#95;dual&#95;mov&#95;b32&quot;                        5</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00741" /><CodeLine lineNumber="741"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// v&#95;dual&#95;mov&#95;b32            v6            0 (DST)    --&gt;      6</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00742" /><CodeLine lineNumber="742"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                           v1            1 (SRC0)   --&gt;      7</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00743" /><CodeLine lineNumber="743"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// -------------------------------------------------------------------</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00744" /><CodeLine lineNumber="744"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00745" /><CodeLine lineNumber="745" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/amdgpu/vopd/componentlayout"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/amdgpu/vopd/componentlayout/#adb8be7174292f0e01011a551255ca154">ComponentLayout</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00746" /><CodeLine lineNumber="746"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">private</span><span class="doxyHighlight">:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00747" /><CodeLine lineNumber="747"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Regular MachineInstr/MCInst operands are ordered as follows:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00748" /><CodeLine lineNumber="748"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   dst, src0 &#91;, other src operands&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00749" /><CodeLine lineNumber="749"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// VOPD MachineInstr/MCInst operands are ordered as follows:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00750" /><CodeLine lineNumber="750"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   dstX, dstY, src0X &#91;, other OpX operands&#93;, src0Y &#91;, other OpY operands&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00751" /><CodeLine lineNumber="751"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Each ComponentKind has operand indices defined below.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00752" /><CodeLine lineNumber="752"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">constexpr</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> MC&#95;DST&#95;IDX&#91;&#93; = &#123;0, 0, 1&#125;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00753" /><CodeLine lineNumber="753"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">constexpr</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> FIRST&#95;MC&#95;SRC&#95;IDX&#91;&#93; = &#123;1, 2, 2 </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; + OpX.MCSrcNum &#42;/</span><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00754" /><CodeLine lineNumber="754"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00755" /><CodeLine lineNumber="755"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Parsed operands of regular instructions are ordered as follows:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00756" /><CodeLine lineNumber="756"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   Mnemo dst src0 &#91;vsrc1 ...&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00757" /><CodeLine lineNumber="757"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Parsed VOPD operands are ordered as follows:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00758" /><CodeLine lineNumber="758"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   OpXMnemo dstX src0X &#91;vsrc1X|imm vsrc1X|vsrc1X imm&#93; &#39;::&#39;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00759" /><CodeLine lineNumber="759"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   OpYMnemo dstY src0Y &#91;vsrc1Y|imm vsrc1Y|vsrc1Y imm&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00760" /><CodeLine lineNumber="760"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Each ComponentKind has operand indices defined below.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00761" /><CodeLine lineNumber="761"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">constexpr</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> PARSED&#95;DST&#95;IDX&#91;&#93; = &#123;1, 1,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00762" /><CodeLine lineNumber="762"><span class="doxyHighlight">                                                4 </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; + OpX.ParsedSrcNum &#42;/</span><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00763" /><CodeLine lineNumber="763"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">constexpr</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> FIRST&#95;PARSED&#95;SRC&#95;IDX&#91;&#93; = &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00764" /><CodeLine lineNumber="764"><span class="doxyHighlight">      2, 2, 5 </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; + OpX.ParsedSrcNum &#42;/</span><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01072" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1072"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     Waitcnt&#91;6:4&#93;   = \\p Expcnt      (pre-gfx11)</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01077" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1077"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     Waitcnt&#91;15:14&#93; = \\p Vmcnt&#91;5:4&#93;  (gfx9,10)</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01285" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1285"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// These functions are considered entrypoints into the current module, i.e. they</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01286" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1286"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// are allowed to be called from outside the current module. This is different</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01287" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1287"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// from isEntryFunctionCC, which is only true for functions that are entered by</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01288" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1288"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the hardware. Module entry points include all entry functions but also</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01289" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1289"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// include functions that can be called from other functions inside or outside</span></CodeLine>
